race.comment: PILLAGER (2) tackled a $50k maiden at Gilgandra last start and didn't do a bad job to be beaten 4.3 lengths after settling midfield. Has had plenty of chances but in a race that lacks depth the form from that last run should stand up. WOLFCRAIG (6) returned from a spell with a close second over 1050m at Inverell on Boxing Day. Lightly raced and open to plenty of improvement. BOLD BENDER (7) has raced 32 times for eight placings. Recent efforts have been unremarkable but in a race of this standard she is a top three hope. WRITTEN LEGACY (12) was safely held first-up at Inverell but can improve out to this distance. The likely leader MISS HEROIC (11) can sneak into the frame on a six-day turnaround.
